text: Now I love Pizza Hut's pizza. Everything is wonderful there I love their lunch buffet I love their food the only thing that I would say is they need to put more toppings on their Pizza especially when you order for them to come to your home they never put enough toppings on it they skip you out for the price but I think after a while they started to pick up and get better because I tell you what it was only like 3 days ago 4 days ago I ordered a pizza from there and when it came to my door and when I had chicken wings to which were great with the bone in butt when they came to my door it was the best pizza I think I've ever had since I've lived here 34 years or more they put so much topping on that I thought I was in heaven and I must have done something right or something but I tell you they need to keep that up if they want their customers they need to start feeling those pizzas with more toppings and the cheese because that's the way a pizza should be you want that cheese just oozing off and all those toppings falling off. Now that's what I call a true pizza and it's worth it if they could just keep that up I think they would be making more money than ever. So I say all you Pizza Lovers you need to go up there try their pizzas try their Buffet try and order some for home and see what happens like I said I don't think we should have to pay for that those extra toppings because what they did that day I was so so happy. Keep it up Pizza Hut you getting better. Hopefully you got some really good Cooks in there now and when they make a pizza they know what they're doing. So now when I order home I don't have to call up there and say wow where is the cheese where is the meat I paid too much money for this kind of a pizza. I say yay somebody finally knows how to make a great wonderful Pizza. I hope that all of you experienced what I have. I'm saying this for all the people Pizza Hut keep up the good work don't send out sorry looking pizzas send out the best pizza you can send out because you want those customers.
business_description: Family-friendly chain known for its made-to-order pizzas.

text:
Nothing came out right! Ordered 3 orders of wings, 3 orders of cheese sticks, 1 order of mozz sticks, and 1 pizza.

One order of wings came out 25 minutes after ordered and were not crispy at all, like they were rushed through the fryer, then 10 minutes later 1 order of cheese sticks.

25 mins later the 2nd order of wings came out and we were asked if everything was ok now? No were still missing 1 order of wings, 2 cheese sticks, I mozz stick and a pizza.

The pizza came out moments later and was greasy and the cheese was barely melted.

The next order of cheese sticks came out and were ice cold with no sauce.

By this time we had had enough, and asked for boxes and the rest to go. The wings came out around the same time and seemed to be ok.

Got to the counter and we were still charged for the things we hadn't revieved. The girl, who was very kind and sweet apologized and took off the things we didn't recieve and gave us a little discount.

All and all we will never go back again!!!

We also werent the only table this happened to the larger table next to us who arrived before us had the same things happen to them!
business_description: Family-friendly chain known for its made-to-order pizzas.

text: I am a regular customer of the delivery service and I am happy with the food and drivers. I worked in this particular store 24 years ago when I met my husband. I stopped in and spoke with a manager about having my son's 10th birthday party there with about 14 people. We brought our own cake and ice cream and we ordered 7 pizzas. It was a Sunday after church and it wasn't crowded and the whole experience was the least stressful birthday party so far! I was so impressed with the waitress and I made sure to be generous with her tip. They held our ice cream in the freezer until we needed it and the pizzas were the best. The prices were so much more reasonable than we expected and much less than other places that offer birthday parties. We didn't book an official pizza party but it was a really great experience and my stress level was so much lower than all 9 previous birthdays! Thank you Pizza Hut! I highly recommend this store for anything you may need because they are very cooperative and they went above and beyond my expectations and they were all so kind. I may have the next 8 parties there! Lol

text: Your experience at Ole Hickory Steak House begins in the parking lot as you park your car and began to smell the charcoal smoke in the air. On the way to the front door you pass by a glass window and see the mouth watering steaks lined up on the grill being seasoned by grill master,  Bobby Bowen. Once inside your are greeted by a host of employees running around in controlled chaos putting out bake potatoes, buttered toast  preparing salads, seating people and the list goes on and on. The decor of the building inside and out has changed very little over the years and neither has the wait staff as they pretty much know what you like to eat and drink even before you even sit down. It's been rated as one of the Top 10 Steak Houses in Ms.

text:
My husband and I just visited this place for the first time. We was not impressed in the slightest. We both ordered large ribeye. He got rare , and I got well done. His steak was a little more tender than mine of course which is to be expected for a little but but not that much toughness. My steak had NO flavor. I had to have sauce just to be able to eat it. The ranch dressing that they give is the bottle ranch, and not the real good kind either. The salad was disappointing. It was literally salad mix out of the store with a slice of tomato on top. They don't have anything else to go on salads, not even pickles. My waitress was not friendly. At one point, my husband asked her for extra butter for our baked potatoes, which we requested when we ordered but didn't receive. When she brought it, my husband told her thank you and it almost seemed as though she wasn't going to respond or acknowledge him. Then She turned around and saw our faces and barked out you're welcome. We would have brushed it off as her personality, which still isn't okay. Then one of the regular customers came in and she was as nice as could be to them and waited on them hand and foot like they were the only people there. Then the waitress came to put steaks on our table, she grabbed the dressing tray and said are you done with this. I said no mam I need the ranch off of it. So she leaves the tray. When she finally decides to come refill our tea, she just picks up the dressing tray without asking if we were done ,which we wasnt, and just walks off. My drink stayed empty for a long while and our waitress came and refilled her regular customers who were beside us, and walked past our table 4 times with a tea jug in hand, then went to go talk to the other employees, then sat down at a table, and then finally came to refill our drinks. I'm sorry, but if you can't be friendly or at least smile to ALL your customers and treat them all like they're important then you don't need to be a waitress or working with the public. We did nothing to cause her to be that way to Us and they were not busy.

We came with the expectation of "VERY GREAT STEAKS AND GREAT SERVICE " but that was not what we got.
This is my personal opinion to Old hickory, but it's very unsanitary to have the same people preparing food, or having their hands anywhere around food, running the register. Also, if a steak is cooked right, you can have a tender and tasty well done steak. The menu says they are not responsible if well done steaks are not tender or tasteless.

I did like how the cook and the guys back there with him all spoke to us when we walked in.
business_description: Old-fashioned, informal chophouse focusing only on steak cooked on an open charcoal grill.

text: Picked up a pizza at Pizza Hut (Brookhaven) about 3 days. Ordered a 3 topping large pizza, with a pan crust. No "pineapple" taste! We usually enjoy our orders from there. Maybe the Covad-19 caused problems with supplies, new employees?!...........Thought  there  would be an improvement 5 or 6 months later. Not! Ordered  medium pan pizza with  several toppings (no spinach available  at all), cinnamon bread sticks, and cheesey breadsticks. ALL ITEMS  UNDER COOKED, NOT EVEN A LITTLE CRISPY CRUNCH ANYWHERE!!!!! PIZZA DID NOT HAVE A GOOD TASTE. WILL BUT PIZZA ELSEWHERE; THIS IS MY LAST STRAW!!!!!!! EVEN THE PAN CRUST NOT TASTY!!!!!

text:
We have long loved going to the "Cock
Of the Walk"on the Ross Barnett Reservoir.  It's just perfect on all
Levels... It's very picturesque with
the beautiful water as a background,
Mallord ducks and Pelicans who love
to be fed by people.  Inside the restaurant has its own charm, with
the nostalgia of River boats and pirates.  The main food everyone goes there to eat is Catfish fried to perfection,and all the fixings that are served with it..."Haw, it is good"!
They even provide entertainment!
Your server , dressed in appropriate
Attire for the time frame in keeping
With the Riverboat period,. Comes out
To your table,with a small skillet of Cornbread, loosens it by running a knife blade and filps it high in the air
And catches it in the skillet.  To my husband and me,  everything about
The "Cock of the walk" Is a perfect place to go to eat and delight all your
Senses!
business_description: Big waterfront seafood restaurant specializing in fried fare served up in rustic, kid-friendly digs.

text: I have alway loved cock of the walk but this time I was very disappointed.  It has been a long time since I have visited but I had a fish craving and I was so sure to go here. Upon entering and being sitted everything started great. After that.....Our table was sticky and still had dried food on it.Our waitress who was nice but seemed very rushed which meant she mixed our order with the table behind us. The tables were too close so she continuously pushed my chair up when passing between tables with no excuse me or anything. When our order was corrected our fish didnt seem done and the french fries and fried pickles all taste like onion rings. Like they were all just fried together. My son got chicken tenders which had no favor at all. When the waitress brought our refills she was moving so fast she never even noticed she wasted drink in my greens.... so to say the least I will not be visiting them again. I just feel like for the price the food should be much better. I have gotten better fish through the drive thru at Penn's.  I just hope in the future they would do much better.

text: As a newbie in Hattiesburg and always on the hunt for healthy restaurants, I came across Sweet Peppers Deli. Nice clean casual setting. I usually order salads from here. They have two sizes, small and large. Lots of options to pick from the menu which also include sandwiches, wraps, soups etc and also have some good dessert options including a variety of different cakes. Staff has been friendly and my order generally does not take long. I usually get a cesar salad with mushrooms added to it. It also has delicious sundried tomatoes in it with large croutons. The cesar dressing tastes like a mix of cesar dressing and ranch, so more on the sweeter side. Always content with my order. Recommend checking it out if you are in the mood for some healthy food.

text: I am always looking for some good and authentic Mexican food and this was my first time trying Del Sol. It seemed to have good ratings. Here's what I can say. The portions are completely out of control. This may be why it is so popular in the most obese state in the US. The chicken Quesadilla was enough for 2-3 people and the special plate could have fed a family. The salsa bowl they bring out to the table with chips was also seemingly wasteful, no way to eat all that. Now for the guacamole, it needed some cilantro, lime and salt.  The margaritas were 2 for 1 but were pretty watered down. If you want HUGE portions that are light on taste, this is probably for you.
business_description: Compact, pared-down fixture in a strip mall providing sizable Mexican dishes along with happy hours.

Always an amazing experience when we come here.  If you're looking for a great, fast meal, you can not go wrong with the typical fare of chimichanga, burrito, and fajita.  I like the carne asada both as an entree and the tacos.  If you're looking for something special, try the molcajete.  It is a pleasant mix of meats, beautifully spiced and accented, plus it's presentation is phenomenal.

Most importantly, service is always great. Very friendly wait staff, always a delight to be around.

They have a large variety of food and i havent ever gotten anything i didnt enjoy. My personal favorite is their quesadillas... text: I was placed on hold when I called to order my pizza, after holding for about 10 minutes I decided to just drive there since I live around the corner. When I pulled up there was one car in the parking lot, 5 people on the clock, one on the phone, one cooking and 3 standing there talking. When I got to the register they eventually broke up and one asked could she take my order, just then the gentleman that was taking an order on the phone hung it up and picked up the other phone which was me on hold. Why there were so many people standing around talking doing nothing while I was on hold is beyond my comprehension. This Pizza hut has had a steady decline in the past year or so, if it wasn't for my daughter I would never go there

Instead of preparing the third Taco they split the meat into three very minut portions. When we ask for additional meat the staff began laughing at us. I exained that I was sincere. Nevertheless,  the staff continued to laugh. The problem was never corrected. My friend and I will not return. Please see the attached pictures for reference and perspective regarding the amount of meat that was on each taco.

text:
Nicely done. Not a huge parking lot. If you are driving an RV, come on a day with few people or park elsewhere and walk here.

The movie was good, but they also have videos in the rest of the displays. You can spend a few hours here if you like civil war history.

On the walk up, they have items embedded into the side walk that zig zags up the hill to replicate the zig zag pattern you would run if you were retreating under fire.   The items might be things you dropped or left behind as you fled. Interesting way to get you thinking before you ever even enter the building.
business_description: Civil War museum dedicated to the Battle of Corinth, offering multimedia exhibits in a modern space.

text: A destination restaurant as you are not likely to stumble across it.  Located off a country road and I definitely recommend locating it first in daylight hours if you are going to drive there at night.   Hard to see entrance and you may be tailgated, so beware.   I went on a cold January Thursday which was advertised as Tapas night.  No Spanish tapas and only a few extra middle size plates, all American, to make it qualify as Tapas.  The interior is very attractive and modern with high ceilings and there was an open fireplace visible from many of the tables. A small pleasant bar area.   Prices are moderately expensive but not out of line with the quality of food and ambience, so I would describe it as a fair value.  Professional staff are well mannered and mostly know their stuff and the menu.   I skipped the large plate selections and had a scallop appetizer w slaw, a large bowl of French onion soup, as distinct from the smaller version listed on the menu, and a creme brulee for dessert.   They were all very satisfactory.  Parking is convenient.
business_description: Carefully sourced contemporary Southern cooking served in a rustic-chic dining room of a log chalet.

text: I took my husband here for his Birthday celebration on a Sunday. Brunch here was wonderful! The service was excellent and the food delighted with a perfect flavor bouquet and lovely presentation. Prices are also reasonable for this level of dining experience. Also, the atmosphere takes you to the quintessential Southern home. It feels like you are in the Gone with the Wind era, and Scarlett will be out any minute. Must visit! Well worth the 45 minute drive from Gulfport!
business_description: Elegant eatery in 2 connected 19th-century cottages offering upscale, globally inspired dishes.

text: Read two reviews and we decided to try it out. There was adequate parking in back. When we got to the host we were asked if we had reservations, which we had not. Neither of the reviews mentioned reservations. We were seated quickly. However we sat for what felt like 30 minutes before our drink order was taken. After that though, everything was on point. We had random Cab with our dinner. It was very good. The BBQ shrimp app was absolutely delicious, with toasted bread for dipping. The cheeses in the Sycamore House salad and Bacon Gorgonzola and Tomato pizza raised everything to a higher level. We did feel a bit under dressed in our t shirts. We will definitely be back.

text: It's been many years since I've been in this historic building. It's where I had my first job some 30 years ago. I started as a busboy and worked my way up to waiter back when it was the Landmark. Needless to say many memories came flooding back when I walked into the building. So many of its features still remain. I was pleased to find it is still that place to have a fine meal in a fine atmosphere. However it is also nice that they offer simpler fare such as pizzas and sushi. I intend to return and become a regular. I'm a little embarrassed to be a bay rat and have been away so long

But it should have been much better and tastier. My wife liked the shrimp and grits but its flavor was not what one would expect for that dish. It was fair to good but with a different flavor than one would expect. The portions were smaller than one would like. The ambience and service was great. I felt for the price we should have gotten more food. A small salad should have been included with the meal. I would give it a second try. text: Starbucks policy, States if ordered through the app, customers are eligible for free refills of coffee or teas regardless of original drink purchase. Today I ordered an iced coffee, and a frappe, for my girlfriend, ( through the app, in-store). I got a refill, no problem with my iced coffee. I informed my girlfriend of Starbucks policy and asked if she wanted me to get her a refill of iced coffee. I was informed, that the location inside the target, in Flowood, Ms. Is a franchise versus a corporate store, and they do not honor Starbuck's refill policy.  I can accept this, but I won't go there again, because I want my refill, I am curious if this a true representation of what a franchise owner wishes to conduct in their store? I want to add: the lady representing the store, tonight, wasn't rude. Her drinks tasted delicious. She politely informed me that they only give refills if the original purchase reflected the refill. I felt disappointed because I was misinformed by someone. Either Starbucks needs to add that franchise stores might not reflect their policies versus cooperate run stores. And highlight on their locator if the store is a franchise. Or the employee gave me the wrong information. And misrepresented the franchise's policy. I only purchased the product because I thought I was getting a good deal due to the policy that wasn't honored.
business_description: Seattle-based coffeehouse chain known for its signature roasts, light bites and WiFi availability.

text: This is my first bad experience with a Marriott property and I travel a lot. The fact that I called to confirm my late check in and was not told at that time that the room I reserved over a month in advance was not available is where it all started. When I arrived to check in I waited in line about 15 minutes, then was just given a key after telling her my name, not asking for an ID or credit card. It wasn't until I got to my room that I find out it was just a single bed, I reserved a double bed because I had someone traveling with me and we both wanted to be comfortable for a 2 night stay, I called the desk and the lady tells me there is nothing they can do there are no more rooms. So I went down and she called the manager since there was not one at the property, she was not much help and didn't offer anything for our inconvenience. She only offered to call the Fairfield to see of they had any doubles left. After being at the desk until after 11 pm, because there was a few bus loads of school kids and their chaperones whose room arrangements weren't right either, I just gave up. The only thing the Fairfield had left was the same room I was already in there. The next morning I never heard anything from the manager or any other staff for that fact. I even went to the desk to let the know that room 219 refrigerator was leaking everywhere. She only wrote it down but no one came to check it. I love Marriott hotels but I won't staying at this one again. Very unapologetically unprofessional and unorganized.
business_description: Straightforward hotel offering a seasonal outdoor pool, plus a business center free WiFi.

As a customer that has ordered from you all several times.. your process has always been good. But this last time the ball was officially dropped. I was concerned with his confusion that he may not pull through with this request so u called the store, man on the other end was polite and so was I. He even said he would put in a new order of wings and have my dressing delivered and it came here in record timing considered he tomr me it would be here in 45 mins.. 20ish mins later here they are at my door, steaming hot wings and guess what... no blue cheese.
Moral of this is everyone gets one chance. I gave it and y'all messed up again.
Improvement definitely needs to be made here.

text:
I moved across town recently and have had to start using this location and I'm not pleased by any means.

I've ordered multiple times and my pizza has shown up cold and I told them I wasn't going to accept cold pizza and when they go to take it back, they never show back up.

I've ordered via phone and via the Pizza Hut website and been promised arrival times that are normally 30 minutes to an hour and a half longer than what was promised upon delivery.

I've ordered a few times and called to check the status and have been told that they never received my order and get up on hold just to be hook up on.

One phone call in particular I was on hold for 22 minutes and then heard someone come back on the line just to hang up without bothering to ask if anyone was still there.

On top of that, I've had multiple occasions where I've tried ordering Dr. Pepper and instead of calling to tell me that they do not have it, they've brought Pepsi or Root Beer in place which would be fine if they had called to tell me but apparently it's just okay in their eyes to just assume it's all soda and who cares what the person paying for it wants.

I've even tried to give back cold pizza or wrong items that were delivered and the driver(s) have said in turn,"You have to pay either way or it comes out of my pocket."

How they remain open is a mystery to me...
business_description: Family-friendly chain known for its made-to-order pizzas.

text: I have tried Gigi's cupcakes before in Flowood, MS. Had a craving for a cupcake, so decided to check out the spot in Hattiesburg. Pretty good sized location. Very clean and staff is friendly. There is a seating area for you to enjoy your cupcake upon purchase. I preferably enjoy the cupcakes with real cream cheese icing. I would say that the cupcake was slightly dry and did not taste as fresh as it usually does. I tried to white midnight magic which is generally my go to cupcake for my sweet tooth. Would give this spot another try hoping for a better day. If no improvements will stick to the flowood location.

text: Excellent place for a meal. A very good buffet. Large selection. The food is always seasoned well. The service is friendly and efficient. Prices are reasonable especially for lunch. Good senior discount. Good military discount. The fried chicken is exceptional. The pot roast is also exceptional. Wonderful desert selection including soft serve ice cream. Full salad bar with additional salads: broccoli, Caesar, and macaroni. Banana pudding is very good as well. The barbeque pork is very good for a buffet.

text: Marco's Pizza has proven to be consistent and high quality. You can't drive up to a window and the are not the fastest. They are not the cheapest, either. However, the toppings are generous, and they are fresh and flavorful. The crust does not taste like cardboard. In fact, it tastes good, bakes well and reminds me of the crust at one of my favorite pizza places growing up. The sauce is robust, and the cheese tastes better than its competitors'. We've switched, and I recommend folks to try them next and decide for yourself.
business_description: Counter-serve chain serving specialty or custom pizzas for takeout or delivery.

text:
I ordered 2 pizzas online. The timeline I was given to pick them up was 5:40-5:50. I ordered them at 5:18. Okay, this is a reasonable time to prepare 2 pizzas. I walk in the store at 5:45. I was not greeted for a few minutes by the guy at the counter. The girl was taking care of a couple that was there when I walked in.  Then the girl walks away. The guy ,,, still standing there. The girl finally told him to wait on me.  I told him I ordered online and told him my name.  He went to the rack and looked at the pizza there. He said that they must still be in the oven. There were 2 boxes on the shelf, that he JUST looked at. AFI I'm waiting for another 10 minutes and ask again about my pizzas.  Could he just check on them? Guess what? Those 2 boxes sitting on thre shelf when I walked in, the ones he looked at? Those were my pizzas, there the whole time
Oh, and I asked about getting some garlic butter, how much, etc. The girl said that it comes with the pizza. I believed her. Got home with my pizzas,finally! and no garlic butter. This was not a good impression. It's a good thing we love the pizza!!
business_description: Counter-serve chain serving specialty or custom pizzas for takeout or delivery.

text: I ordered a personal pan pizza. I was told it would be ready in 10 to 15 minutes. I pulled in a parking place and waited 15 minutes before pulling back around to the window. The car in front of me had been waiting almost an hour for theirs. I waited and waited. I finally got out of my vehicle and walked to the window. I paid for my pizza when I ordered. There was no one at the window and I called out several times and was finally answered that she would be there in a few minutes. She told me to go back to my vehicle which I did. I still say and waited. They were not busy, just myself and one other vehicle. Thirty five minutes later I FINALLY get my pizza. When I get home and open, it is burnt around the edges and not cut completely through so I could pick it up. Oh I forgot to mention I asked for napkins and was told that they were out of them. LOUSY SERVICE AND PIZZA. Next time I will drive to Papa John's in Oxford.

text: Today was started out mowing grass at home. We traveled to Tupelo to get a few things. We ended up stopping to eat here at Harvey's.  We both had the cajun pasta dishes. One was chicken and the other was shrimp and crawfish. Excellent meals to order ! We also tried a glass of wine each. I had the Leftie Maiden Voyage white blend. My wife had the queens mead noir. Excellent wines to have these meals. Great pricing for the working family these days. Over all I recommend this restaurant to any and all. The appearance of this restaurant is so beautifully designed and elegantly laid out. Guys if your looking for a romantic evening for a first date, an anniversary,  or just a night out with the wife, or guys proposing to that special someone here would be a great place. Again 5 stars for Harvey's.  Also our waiter Greg was professional and courteous. God bless America !!!

text: This place was posted on North Ms honest restaurant reviews and was highly rated, I decided to take my Husband there yesterday for Father's day and it didn't disappoint. The staff was friendly, prompt and professional. The 14oz ribeye was grilled to a perfect medium rare and I was very satisfied, because I was awaiting to discover the often presented medium well steaks I often receive from other places. It was very delicious. I chose the mashed potatoes for my side, along with the side house salad. My Husband chose the Shrimp and grits and that was a very good choice and his side of mac and cheese was amazing as well. We bought the kids the chicken tenders and my husband and I were surprised to find that they were extremely tender and very juicy. Last but not least, we seen some really good reviews on the Broccoli bites, so we decided to get those as the appetizer! I will say we have never had anything like it and will get those every time we stop in! Very delicious by far. We enjoyed our experience and will recommend.

text: I normally would not take time to negatively review a Buisness but this one deserves it. I called at 9:45 and after completing my entire order and also paying via credit card, was told it would be 30 minutes and the phone call ended. They called back at 9:52 to let me know they didn't have a delivery person so I offered to come pick it up but then they said they were closed. I asked what time they close and they said 10 so at that point I asked to speak to a manager. The manager got on the phone and said she had shut her registers down and they were closed. I brought it to her attention that it wasn't  closing time and I said so you closed your register 15 minutes early and she hung up on me. Not professional at all. That was very unprofessional of a person in a managerial position. I know what it's like to work with the public and have a certain time to hope to walk out that door and the day end but when you're in customer service that is something that comes with it. I will be calling higher management tomorrow because I'm almost positive that what this manager did is completely against policy.

text:
It seems a strange management style, and I have no idea why a restaurant would ensure that dine-in customers have horrible service, but it seems that this Pizza Hut is deliberately shooing off diners who want to do more than just pick up a pie at the drive-thru window.
I've been to this restaurant several times in the few years since they opened this brand new place. And each time I eat there, there are fewer customers in the house. This time it was a trio of ladies and my party. No other diners came in during our 80-minute visit.
Do the owners deliberately hire inept servers to cut down on dining guests? If so, why did they build a whole restaurant instead of a small shop?
At one point my wife had to get her own drink refill from the server station. Where our server disappeared to is a mystery - not like he had a lot of tables to attend.
The food is classic Pizza Hut. If you like drive-thru or delivery then this is a great place.
If you enjoy the experience of dining out, maybe not so much.
business_description: Family-friendly chain known for its made-to-order pizzas.

text: My husband and I enjoyed visiting the home of Medgar and Merlie Evers. This visit was very insightful and educational. I would advise everyone to take their children to see this history.
business_name: Medgar and Myrlie Evers Home National Monument
business_description: Preserved home of assassinated civil rights icon Medgar Evers, with tours available by appointment.

text: Mrs. Minnie Watson is Exceptional! The information given on this tour was informative and riveting! She told Medgar Evers' story to us in great detail.
business_name: Medgar and Myrlie Evers Home National Monument
business_description: Preserved home of assassinated civil rights icon Medgar Evers, with tours available by appointment.

text: It's in my community.
business_name: Medgar and Myrlie Evers Home National Monument
business_description: Preserved home of assassinated civil rights icon Medgar Evers, with tours available by appointment.

text: We really enjoyed the visit. Tougaloo College has done an excellent job preserving this piece of history.
business_name: Medgar and Myrlie Evers Home National Monument
business_description: Preserved home of assassinated civil rights icon Medgar Evers, with tours available by appointment.

text: Visiting the Medgar Evers house was a highlight of our Southern civil rights history road trip...thanks to Ms. Minnie Watson, the docent who made the whole visit worthwhile. She knew Medgar Evers personally, she lives in the community, she narrates both the man and his time in history, as well as bringing the story to the present day. Ms. Watson makes this 'historic' site seem very real and very present-day. Of all the houses, plantations, and museums we visited this is by far the smallest--it's a very modest ranch-style home---but the story and the man are as powerful as it gets.It is imperative that you call ahead and book an appointment. This is not-to-be-missed opportunity to hear history and interpretation from someone who lived it.
business_name: Medgar and Myrlie Evers Home National Monument
business_description: Preserved home of assassinated civil rights icon Medgar Evers, with tours available by appointment.

text: This is the home of famed civil rights leader Medgar Wiley Evers. The Jackson International Airport among a few other things have been named after him. His home where he was assassinated has been turned into a museum. It is a pure time capsule left just as it was when he was murdered and still full of all the families belongings and such. Another great option if you like this kind of thing is to check out the newly opened Civil Rights Museum in downtown Jackson also.
business_name: Medgar and Myrlie Evers Home National Monument
business_description: Preserved home of assassinated civil rights icon Medgar Evers, with tours available by appointment.

text:
This place was open for dining in and had great Google reviews.   We gave it a shot.  Called up and oddly they didn't take a reservation (though they do) but said to not come before 8 P.M.

Well at exactly 8 we arrived and were immediately offered a seat in the courtyard.  It was just lovely out there.  Nice temperature at that hour and a cool breeze.  Keep in mind it is the middle of June.

Dogs are welcome out there too!

Our host was so sweet and he introduced us to the server, and I wish I remembered her name.  I think she does some teaching too?  We heard the specials and immediately dropped our menus and went for it.

The hangar steak was perfectly done to requested temperature and crazy delicious!  The lamb chops (rack) came with 6 and with a strawberry glaze.  WOW!  Our sides were 2 each:  both got the beets, which were in a syrup like sauce without adding anything weird to the flavor... maybe it was puree of beet?  Whatever it was we loved it.  One got the cauliflower which came in a ramekin sort of mashed potato style.  I could have eaten a bowl of that.  And lastly one got the grilled mushrooms and onions.  Also good, but nothing beyond the description.

Do yourself a favor and go to this restaurant.  Besides the food, the service and everyone working there added to the wonderful experience.

text:
What can I say? You get what you pay for. You got the big bucks in town? Take your wife or girlfriend or mistress here and you're not going to be disappointed.

They got this menu thats always rotating, so it keeps the place fresh. Gourmet food at its finest, man it felt like I was in NYC when I was here. The wait staff is personal, the mood is great, drink selections above standards.

Needless to say; you aren't going to be disappointed: UNLESS you don't reserve a table. But, make sure to reserve your table and spot because youre not going to want to miss what they got going on here.

This is one of the only restaurants in town to truly cook your food to order, and the palette will not disappoint you. So if you're looking for a romantic, or extreme business sit in, i whole heartedly recommend this place. Compliments to the chef and the cooking team.

text:
This is probably the best restaurant I have eaten at in the last year.

The atmosphere is very pleasant.  Spacing between the tables was perfect given current concerns.  The tables were set with quality tablecloths and place settings.

The food was incredible.  The portions were perfectly sized.  I had an eight ounce filet which was generously cut.  All of the dishes arrived at our table piping hot.

I often leave higher priced restaurants feeling slightly robbed.  This is a place where you leave feeling that your money was well spent.

The old fashioned I had from the bar was perfectly prepared.  I can only comment on the desserts to say that they looked wonderful.

Sep 2020. We come back again and we enjoy every bit of the time here. The food is great. I ordered filet and it was cook just right!! My friend ordered the almond trout. It is crisp and tenderly juice!
DEC. I usually do not complain but this is a very uneasy experience on a "Valentine day". I did make resevation at 7pm and I arrived at 6:45pm. All 7pm guest were seated including many people who come after 7pm. Our group was seated at 7:20pm. We were put to seat outside the patio in cold wind and rain close to those trees. We saw two or more table are wide opened inside. The sweet lady at the entrance told us she would do anything to resolve the problem, but not able to let our group sit inside. We were just not dress warm enough to seat out the cold weather. After 5mins in the cold my 76 years old mom start sneezing. We choose to left Chimney WITHOUT eating our  Valentine dinner. We were very disappointed.
But the owner called us. Sincerely apologize to our experience. He even send us a coupon without expectation!  So we decided to go back. This time those food were wonderful,  specially the fried oyster. The filet mignon was outstanding! The steak was just right! This time, we were service well! We were very happy, so we gave a big tips to the waitress.  They earn me back!

The service on this particular day was fantastic. Our waiter made sure our drinks were full and checked on us frequently, yet allowed us to enjoy our Sunday lunch. text:
Their Tuesday night buffet doesn't start until 6:00 (a little late for families with young kids). We arrived about 6:30 and in spite of the fact that no one was there, we had to wait almost 5 minutes for someone to come out and seat us. The waitress never greeted us, never smiled, barely looked at us. She acted like we were ruining her day.
Every pizza on the buffet was pepperoni. Either just pepperoni, pepperoni and sausage, or pepperoni and onions and peppers. We were 4 adults and 2 kids and the kids especially were not happy with pepperoni. We asked the waitress if they were going to put out anything without pepperoni and she turned her back, and as she walked away said yes. Still, when we left, EVERYTHING had pepperoni!
We had ordered 3 drinks for the adults, but only 1 of us got a refill. She ignored the empty glasses the other 2 of us had! Still, she never brought the bill and only gave me the receipt AFTER I paid and I saw that she charged us for 4 drinks. Also, kids are supposed to be free and she charged us for 1 of them.
I don't think I've ever stiffed a waitperson a tip, even with bad service, but I couldn't bring myself to give her even a penny after putting up with her attitude and then seeing how much she over charged. I knew arguing with her would only make the heartburn from the pizza worse. Besides, I will NEVER eat at this restaurant again!
business_description: Family-friendly chain known for its made-to-order pizzas.

text:
Put in my order 10 minutes out for some chicken and waffles. When I got there my order was hot and ready! Chicken was nice and crispy, fried perfectly, not one dry wing. Batter was golden brown, it was almost too pretty to eat. Chicken didn't have way too much seasoning, which paired really well with the waffle. The syrup wasn't overly sweet, the balance in flavors were great, not one thing was fighting for the spotlight, they all wanted to be in the group play together haha. I like my waffles a little bit more crispy on the outside, I'll request that next time. Now, that breakfast biscuit took my breath away, she's a sexy little thing...

Good, fast service. Clean place with lots of seatings indoor and outdoor patio. We weren't sure if we had to pay for meter parking. That buster meter ate my quarter so quick!...at least you know, you don't have to donate your money to that buster stealing meter.
business_description: Hearty plates of soul food doled out in compact, counter-serve digs with outdoor seating.

text: Guy Fieri needs to make a visit this place is awesome! We came for breakfast and left FULL. We had the Sugars full breakfast grits bacon eggs and toast. The kids had waffles. My friend, being from up North exclaimed these are the best grits I've ever had. This coming from a "Yankee" I would have to say if I lived in the area it would definitely be a go to place. Wish we were going to be in town and have lunch here. All I can say is if you are here you need to stop, and Guy you need to stop in!!

text:
Edit: Review was written while still frustrated and it shows in the spelling and grammar.
My experience there was frustrating. I placed a mobile order as soon as I parked for a customized venti Pike Place coffee. I waited a few seconds and walked in because coffee rarely takes more than a few seconds. I walk in and walk to the mobile order area to look for my coffee. I do not see it anywhere so I stand around waiting for about 10 minutes. I thought they were brewing some Pike. Finally, one of the guys notice me waiting and asked me what I was waiting for and I tell him I have a mobile order for a Pike Place. He starts to get it but one of the girls steps up and pulls my coffee out from behind the short wall on the counter where it has been hidden the whole time I was there I'm guessing. It was in the very corner of the short wall so it couldn't be seen from either side by the customer looking for their order. I'm not sure what the purpose is in hiding there customer's mobile order is exactly. The Starbucks on Main St. puts it where you can see it and get it and go.
By then I'm irritated and they give me a coffee cup with no sleeve so now I start looking for the sleeves. I don't see them on the counter anywhere so I go look where the sugar and creamer is. It's not there either. After irritably walking around the store with my coffee, which is actually lukewarm and didn't need a cup sleeve anyway, I finally notice that they have the dispenser on the counter on their side. At every Starbucks I gone to cup sleeves are openly available without resorting to reaching across the counter or begging for one. So I reach across and tear one out of the dispenser. Now of course I didn't actually need one of course because my coffee is lukewarm but I like to have one as a barrier so I don't get anything sticky on my hands. And I don't appreciate having to put that much effort in a transaction that should have been effortless. I should have walked in and my order should have appeared in a spot that customer can actually see and pick up my coffee and be able to grab a cup sleeve and go.
Also I would figure if a customer walks in and immediately goes to the mobile order area or in that general area and doesn't go to the other end to place an order then he must have the mobile order.
Just my 2 cents.
business_description: Seattle-based coffeehouse chain known for its signature roasts, light bites and WiFi availability.

On the meat side of things there is chicken, beef, steak and even carnitas(pork). All the toppings you can think of mutiple types of pico and dressings. Awsome tasteing chips are given with each order to which you can go to the salsa bar that has multiple types of salsa. I personally like the medium tradional and pineapple salsa. Great place the wife and I have eaten at the midtown and Southaven restaurants both places greeted us when we walked in and the staff were super friendly and accommodating.

text:
Exact same review as for the library. It is on the same property.

They have done a great many repairs since Hurricane Katrina damaged it so much in 2005. It faces the Gulf of Mexico. I am currently listening to the podcast "1865" which discusses the assassination of Abraham Lincoln, and the repercussions and how the ending of the Civil War came to an unraveling so much.

Jefferson Davis may have been the 1st and only President of the Confederacy, the emphasis here is on the states rights, specifically to own slaves. This is a narrow view of states rights, but the only one they held. I missed out on the beginning of the tour, but what I did get was informative, if a bit too narrow. The grounds, cemetery and library are immaculate, and this should be enough of a testament.

The staff members are very friendly, this is a good place. I just think that the view of the history should be broader, especially when so many are still disenfranchised even in 2019. I would suggest coming here to see it as a reminder of the past and that it should not be repeated. There are reenactments, though I have not seen it, I would be interested. Pretty informative.
business_description: State museum featuring artifacts related to Confederate President Jefferson Davis.

text:
I might just start driving a little further to the other Starbucks by Wholefoods. I came in today around 7pm. I asked for two pumps of caramel sweetener and the guy today gave me NONE. My bf took a sip and said there's not even a slightest of sugar in it. I brought it back in to be remade. The guy said "I personally made it myself, I did put 2 pumps. If I put 2 pumps and you don't taste it then...uhh I don't know." I ALWAYS ALWAYS HAVE ORDERED TWO PUMPS IN THE LAST 15 YEARS WITH STARBUCKS.

He was being sarcastic and showed me the sweetener and said "Not trying to be a smart allic, but I want you to watch me put in two pumps." Yes you are being a smart ass doesn't matter how you put it. Anyway, it came out the way it should taste. I can close my eyes and be able to tell if my frap has 1 pump, 2 pumps, 3 pumps or the regular 4 pumps. I've had it enough to know it like the back of my hands.

We're human, we make mistakes. If you forgot then you did, but don't show it to my face and slowly count "One...two..." btw they completely forgot the girls drink that came in before me. I had to let them know that she's still sitting there.
business_description: Seattle-based coffeehouse chain known for its signature roasts, light bites and WiFi availability.

text: This is a nice restaurant with great service.  Our waiter was very friendly and knowledgeable about the menu and cocktails.  The manager was also very friendly and even answered questions about services for Father's Day. The pomegranate martini was very good as well as the cheesecake.  Beware the cheesecake is rich and definitely for sharing.  The shrimp and salmon was delicious, we were able to substitute broccoli for the rice that normally accompanies this dish.  The short rib ravioli was disappointing.  The ravioli itself is delicious but the sauce with the horseradish overwhelms the dish so all you can taste is horseradish.  Once I was able to scrape it to the side I was able to taste the veal reduction and ravioli itself.  Note the menu did say it has horseradish but I didn't expect it to overwhelm the whole dish.  The ravioli dish is the only reason this was bumped to 3 stars.

text:
Pretty simple concept, build it yourself and they'll have it ready in 5mins. They have a ton of ingredients for you to mix up your pizza everytime you visit. My bf and I likes different kinds of pizza, he's all meat and cheese and I'm an all wheat crust veggie girl. We end up getting stuck with a big pizza so this is an awesome idea! My family, friends and I tried it and we'd definitely be back.

One small critique, that the people prepping the pizza to evenly spread out the ingredients. Some slices I had a ton sun dried tomatoes and some slices I had none. I like a lot of veggies on mine, so cooking it in 5 minutes, my pizza wasn't hot like it should be.

text: Piccadilly Cafeteria in McComb Ms has great food and exceptional customer service.  I had their fried chicken which was seasoned well, with creamy broccoli and cheese casserole, velvety carrot souffle, soft buttered roll, a slice of chocolate cake, and fruit punch mixed with a bit of sprite for zazz to wash it all down! If you're looking for great food and an awesome dining experience stop by and ask for Toni..she's wonderful!

The chicken breast was a small fillet that was warmed up and sprinkled with blackened seasoning. With the burgers and steaks they have there, it could have been easily grilled. text: Food wise Piccadilly deserves five stars. The only downside that makes me only give it 4 stars is the prices which have steadily risen higher and higher over the years, and generally feel a bit out of control. Though they are not the highest restaurant in the city they could do better on this one aspect. Otherwise they are a wonderful cafeteria style restaurant. They have great customer service nice ambiance topped by real plants and two televisions to enjoy as you eat. They also generally have a large food and dessert collection to choose from. All in all not a bad place to eat.

Don't go by the exterior looks. There is a historic shop inside. The food is surprisingly good. Try the shrimp po-boy.
They also have karaoke on the weekends and are frequented by a very faithful group of customers. The people are genuinely nice and warm and would make you feel right at home.
They have a wide collection of beers. Since it used to be a gas station cum convenience store, the beers are still stored in the fridge and customers can just grab one of their choice and pay at the bar. Totally worth a visit.

text: I have lived in this city for 2 decades but it wasn't until 2019 that I finally decided to eat at the Klondike with my girlfriend. Now, keep in mind that she has really high standards when it comes to sitdown restaurants and she doesn't like most of them. This place though....well its the best in Vicksburg for the both of us. The food is damn good, I always recommend the steak sandwich, and the service is polite, friendly, and prompt...very prompt. Also, the pricing is good, the steak sandwich is 12....which is better than most. The last part of this review is about the asthetic, which is on point. Have you ever wanted CrackerBarrel but without the sad corporate aspects? Well this is it!

text: It's been a while since I last went to Red Lobster. After my recent visit, I'll never go back. This is a chain restaurant that has never been netter than average. However, I i used to like to go because, for the money, it was pretty good. Not anymore.  We took a party of 12 and there was very little traffic at the restaurant that day. It was a Saturday afternoon. They pushed a round 6 top next to a smaller square 4 top and tried to cram us in. We took it upon ourselves to add an empty 4 top to get us seated. After 90 minutes we were still waiting for our food. When it arrived most of it had been sitting for quite a while and was little more than room temperature. A quick survey revealed less than half was a proper temperature. The prices are pretty close to what you see at a much more upscale restaurant. In all, the food was bland, uninspired and expensive for the quality. Our server was nice. He did a fairly decent job. We could have had a better meal for at least a hundred less dollars next door at Olive Garden and I'm no fan of Olive Garden.

text:
We ate the most delicious food at Red  Lobster yesterday...about 3 p.m.  It was served each course at the time, by
A young Server named Ebonly...she was truly a pro and it wasn't until we had nearly finished with our meal, before we learned it was her first day serving on herself.
She was so friendly and great help as we asked for suggestions.  Everything, she suggested was wonderful!  You start off with a bowl of soup... I had selected potato and bacon soup and (Haw!  It was fine!). Ebony, had just made believers out of it.  Wes was about to select Crabmeat soup.  In a polite ,way, she explained that either the cook was not in  the same one or it
Watered down...she was right again, Wes loved the soup!  Red Lobster is well know for it's delicious cheese biscuits and they are still Divine!  As my main entry.. I wanted the"Conconut
Shrinp " with a speacial coconut dip to go with it!  It was was made with a coconut, pineapple  and a white sauce was douglish,.! We had a salad or coleslaw.  I loved the coleslaw and was asked to try some more which they wanted to see which coleslaw.that coustomers liked the most.  I agreed to try, but this one wasn't as good as the first coleslaw that I had.  Then came the desert!  Apple pie all pie with Ice cream...it was a 10 for sure.!  Ebony said that the servers had to make the desserts...she did great!
Looking for delicious food and an enjoyable time...Red Lobster, is a must!

text:
If they have the merchandise you want in a store near you you have to pick it up they will not ship it. I ended up having to wait about 20 minutes for my "already paid for" items after waiting 15 minutes in the checkout line because that's where you pick up your order. The employee couldn't have been nicer and apologized several times for the wait.  Personally I shop online so I don't have to go to the store, I don't have to wait in line and it's automatically shipped to my home.  Old Navy cut themselves out of my list of stores today.
The only reason I'm doing three stars is because the employee was trying so hard. Apparently Old Navy sends an email saying your order is ready but it is not really.  It is only being put together. Hence the wait.  Farewell old friend.

text:
The building needs some work. The ceiling is leaking over the buffet bar.  The pizza is good and service is friendly, but the building itself feels dirty and in bad repair.

Update: The leaky spot over the buffet has been repaired.  You wouldn't know there had been a leak now if you hadn't seen it.  The pizza is good and the service is friendly, but there is still room for improvement.  I've seen the same 3 employees running that place each time I've been there in the last few years.  Melissa works hard to wait the entire dining room alone, and often ends up bussing tables as well.  It's clear that it's just too much for one person when the lunch rush fills the building.  I think that is part of why the building feels dirty.  The building is just old and the lack of natural light doesn't help matters any.  Finding people that are willing to work, and that work hard is a challenge, but I hope they can get someone in there to help.  We were told to seat ourselves, but had to wait at a dirty table for it to be bussed and cleaned.

Another update: February 2019
The ceiling over the buffet had been repaired, but the problem still exists.  The last time I was in there for lunch, that fresh paint on the ceiling was bubbled and looked like it must be holding water.  I enjoy the pizza, and Melissa's service is still great, but someone needs to work on this building!  I would imagine that the people actually managing and working this location have little control over the maintenance of the structure itself.  Pizza hut corporation needs to shut this location down, FIX THAT LEAK OVER THE BUFFET, and do some remodeling, like new carpet.  I've not eaten in any other pizza hut location, so maybe they are all the same dark, cavernous feel inside... But it would be great if there were more natural light in this building.  There are a few small windows along the front, but that is not sufficient.  I would describe it as feeling like I'm eating pizza in a bar.  I've attached a picture to show the bubbled ceiling over the buffet - watch what you eat because that paint isn't going to hold that water forever - and you can see that the building is dark.  The only lighting in the ceiling is a fixture over the buffet and the rest are pendants hanging over each table.  I don't think the cavernous feel would bother me quite as much if I didn't feel like the whole building were dirty and the grime is hidden by the lack of light.

text: If you want good apps or ok milkshakes this place is good. If you want a good Burger go elsewhere. Me and my wife went and ordered the chilli fries and they were great. text:
How can one not love this place?  It's Starkville and MSU tradition, and a delightful greasy spoon, to boot!  Step right in to a warm, homey atmosphere and the best breakfast in town.

Although they get super busy almost every day, it's usually worth the wait.  Having had both breakfast and lunch here, I can say both are quite good.  The blue plate specials are solid, although the food does tend to be a bit greasy.  That's just part of the charm.

Breakfast is the shining star, though.  Fluffy pancakes, crispy hash browns, and eggs however you like them.  Check out the biscuits - a southern classic.  Be like me and get sweet tea for breakfast; it's strong and delicious.  Bacon is always crispy, but if you're a sausage person...you MUST get the sausage.  It's homemade, and some of the best sausage ever.  Keep your eyes peeled for Starkville "celebrities" here -- I'll never forget visiting one morning when the whole girls basketball team rolled in!  Teaire McCowan is a beast, and I love all the other girls, too.  Hail State and Go Dawgs!  :)
business_description: Homestyle American plates served from morning to night in a humble space with an old-timey vibe.

text:
This specific location is... well, it's bad, guys.  The second drive through station seems "closed", but it's lit up and no indication that it's closed.  I drive around to go inside, nearly slip and fall inside the door on some kind of nasty grease or oil or something, which goes halfway up to the counter.  The employees who were actually present in the lobby seemed unconcerned with this.

Aside from these issues with the physical site, they are now consistently messing up orders, and frequently running out of menu items.

Do yourself a favor, and skip this place.  There's a few Sonics (one right next door) that do a better job.  If you must have Whataburger itself, best bet is north at the I-55 exit on County Line Road.

text: I woke up super late and didn't want to cook breakfast, and I realized that  other restaurants had stopped selling breakfast because it was after 10:30..I remembered seeing signage that Whataburger served breakfast from 11pm-11am, so I hurried there.. I arrived in the Drive-Thru at 10:54 a.m.. There was a little mix up at the speaker and it took them about three minutes to answer and I was afraid they were going to tell me I could not get breakfast. But I was able to order it and boy was it DELICIOUS.. I was concerned about the food being old since it was only like 3 minutes left for them to  stop serving breakfast,  but it was piping hot !!There sausage egg and cheese biscuits are the bomb along with the hash brown sticks... I was  glad that I did not get a chance to go to McDonald's for  breakfast because this is hands-down the best breakfast ever from a fast food restaurant!!

text: Food tastes like sonic. I ordered Snapple and lemon pie for dessert. I ate my meal, proceed to take a bite of the lemon pie and it is hard as a rock I had to rip at it with my teeth like a jerkey stick. By that time I realize something I ant right then the taste set in. I nearly vomited and had to spit it out. The filling supposedly lemon was dark as motor oil and literally tasted just like the smell of a building that was just built (paint, wood, concrete, sawdust, chemicals). I've never tasted something so rancid in my life. It was horribly gross. For sake of the establishment I didn't post a photo bc I may have been 1:1,000,000 it happened to. I don't care. I just stopped the waitress me pointed at it she immediately informed her manager. The nicely offered a different dessert but my stomach wouldn't accept anything else nor will it the rest of the day probably. I can't get the taste out of my mouth. I have so very sensitive sense of smell so it was just that much worse. The place was clean(smelled newly built looked it too), employee was nice, and the food was not bad. Just a bad experience. I'm giving 2 stars simply because I feel stuff like that should be caught before a customer does. It has affected the Chance of me coming Back and forever changed how a pie tastes at fast food.

I finally saw Celeste( another server that over known since she was a child) and asked her can she get my server for me. I just thought to myself, "He just missed his blessing, NO TIP." I then tried to place my order after almost 30 min of being there and both items that I tried to order, THEY DIDN'T HAVE!!! text:
My husband and i stopped in this past Friday night.  The service wss pretty slow even though they were not busy. But the waitress was pretty nice when she finally got to our table.  We ordered the nachos and club sandwich. I have always loved their club sandwich.  When wee got the sandwich,  it was on wheat bread and was missing the ham. Basically we recieved a turkey and bacon sandwich, not a club.  I asked the waitress about it and she said yoy only get all 3 meats on the CALI CLUB SANDWICH, along with avocado.  She never asked if we wanted to correct this. Even though i told her i was expecting white bread and all 3 meats.  It was like she didn't care.
But three nachos were awesome.

They ordered a burger and fries to bring home to me. The "all the way" burger was bread meat and cheese, and the fry potion wouldn't fill a small fry bag at McDees. text: I suggested dennys yesterday and went there the first thing I did was grab the menu so I can place my order and the first thing I noticed was the change in the menu and how Alot of the dishes was taken off of there,  I really wanted to go for the skillet with the Gouda cheese and I saw only two skillet dishes one spicy and one with the Bourbon.  I also noticed that you guys have more burgers on the menu and the last thing we need is another burger joint,  we got plenty of those and I use to love coming to you guys because of the variety that you had dennys had everything from chicken to beef now our choices are very slim. I was not in the mood for a burger but ended up getting one because we where hungry and didn't have much of a choice on the menu. I hate that what was once a 5 star ended being a one star in my book I  can only hope that you all focus on variety verses a burger joint you guys can do better than this.

text:
The exhibits are amazing, and it really delves into the specifics about Mississippi during this time period. The entire museum focuses specifically on Mississippi (not the rest of the South) and the Civil Rights leaders from here. It is a museum for Mississippians to know the truth about their heritage and make sure we challenge lies and idolized versions of the past.

The information doesn't pull any punches, rightly so, about the place of African-Americans in Mississippi before the Civil Rights Movement, and their fight for rights during the Civil Rights Movement. The Closed Society exhibit was the most difficult to go through, but it is presented in a way that illustrates the poignancy of that time and shows why this is so important. As a resident of Mississippi, I say all this and add that this is a museum that Mississippi needed for a LONG time. If you have the opportunity, you need to visit it.
business_description: History museum with interactive galleries exploring the state's role in the civil rights movement.

text:
I'm from MS.  Took MS history in school 25 years ago.  We weren't taught all of this, or if we were, it didn't stick.  Or I wasn't ready to hear it as an 8th grader.

This museum is world class.  I don't know what I was expecting, but nothing this well done in my home state.  I always expect half done efforts, and I'm usually disappointed.  But this museum is top knotch.

I did get a bit fatigued toward the end because it is just so much information and reading.  The little shows and experiences are a nice break from reading all the happenings.

The museum has made me appreciate things much more.  And I'm definitely going to read up more on our history as a state.

We've come a long way in such a short time.  We've still got to finish up the fine details.

Also, leave your pocket knives in your car.  I saw the sign, then saw the metal detector and had to turn around to go put my knife in my car.  Came back to security guards and a police officer to see me through the detector.  I'm just a normal southern guy.  We carry pocket knives.  I'm not a threat.  It was humourous to me, but I guess people are crazy these days and you can't be too careful.  Maybe posting about a metal detector and no knives in the parking garage would be a good idea.

text: It makes me sad to give a location such a poor review... But trip after trip, this is one of the worst drive thru's I have ever experienced in speed and efficiency. This drive thru is so lacking. I love wataburger's food, but almost without fail the order is wrong when we go to this location drive thru. Most of the time we just leave with our wrong order, but last night I requested they fix it. It took probably more than 7 or 8 min to order 4 kids meals. It was repeated back several times, the last time finally correct only to get the order and it was wrong. I try really hard to not be a difficult customer and give people the benefit of a doubt, maybe he was new. But someone should have been assisting him, their should have been some guidance... They did make the changes with a smile at the window, but a drive thru with no one if front of us should not push anywhere close to 20 mins. This is not the first time we have had the same issue, but it will probably be the last. I'm not sure we will go back to this drive thru ever. Definitely not when we are trying to hurry so we can get home and put kiddos to bed. I think some of the issue is they are under staffed, lack supervision, direction and apparently lack training.
